This is a demonstration project for a PyYYC presentation on using
Selenium with py.test

Selenium: http://docs.seleniumhq.org/projects/webdriver/
 py.test: http://pytest.org/latest/

setup
-----

- create a virtualenv: ``virtualenv venv``
- activate it: ``source ./venv/bin/activate``
- install things: ``pip install -r requirements.txt``

If it worked you should be able to type ``py.test --help`` and see
something useful.


browser setup
-------------

You should have reasonably new Firefox and Chrome installed, and also
install "chromedriver" (http://chromedriver.storage.googleapis.com) if
you wish to see Selenium drive both Firefox **and** Chrome.



run some tests
--------------

py.test test_github.py


other things to try
-------------------

py.test -s -v test_fixturedemo0.py
py.test -h
py.test --fixtures
py.test --markers

